00:13:38.860 --> 00:13:42.684
Title II crowdfunding where

284
00:13:42.684 --> 00:13:45.160
in order to invest
through that portal,

285
00:13:45.160 --> 00:13:47.230
you have to go through
a process that they

286
00:13:47.230 --> 00:13:51.880
oversee where you
verify tax returns,

287
00:13:51.880 --> 00:13:54.640
you verify that you
have the income or

288
00:13:54.640 --> 00:13:56.995
wealth to be
an accredited investor.

289
00:13:56.995 --> 00:14:00.400
Once they've taken
care of that piece,

290
00:14:00.400 --> 00:14:03.070
then the startups can go to

291
00:14:03.070 --> 00:14:06.280
that website and they know
that well the website has

292
00:14:06.280 --> 00:14:08.920
done that vetting for

293
00:14:08.920 --> 00:14:12.100
them and now they
can raise money from

294
00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:18.685
those investors legally
while staying private.

295
00:14:18.685 --> 00:14:23.350
So Title II is a flavor
of crowdfunding,

296
00:14:23.350 --> 00:14:25.225
but just remember, Title II

297
00:14:25.225 --> 00:14:28.765
is crowdfunding for rich people.

298
00:14:28.765 --> 00:14:30.850
That brings this Title III,

299
00:14:30.850 --> 00:14:32.545
which is just crowdfunding
for everybody.

300
00:14:32.545 --> 00:14:40.660
So Title III says that I can
raise money from anybody.

301
00:14:40.660 --> 00:14:45.205
But now, relative to title II,

302
00:14:45.205 --> 00:14:47.290
there are some restrictions that

303
00:14:47.290 --> 00:14:49.510
we're going to have
to live under.

304
00:14:49.510 --> 00:14:51.685
So yes, I could raise
money from anybody,

305
00:14:51.685 --> 00:14:56.320
but people are
going to be limited

306
00:14:56.320 --> 00:14:58.600
in how much they can invest
and that limit's going to be

307
00:14:58.600 --> 00:15:01.195
a function of
their wealth or income.

308
00:15:01.195 --> 00:15:03.460
Also, I'm going to be limited

309
00:15:03.460 --> 00:15:06.040
in how much money I can raise.

310
00:15:06.040 --> 00:15:09.850
So to think about Title III,

311
00:15:09.850 --> 00:15:14.410
bear in mind that
the regulators care about,

312
00:15:14.410 --> 00:15:18.070
all investors, but
they particularly care

313
00:15:18.070 --> 00:15:21.595
about investors of limited means.

314
00:15:21.595 --> 00:15:24.040
That's what this whole accredited

315
00:15:24.040 --> 00:15:25.360
investor thing is all about.

316
00:15:25.360 --> 00:15:26.590
Well, if you're wealthy enough,

317
00:15:26.590 --> 00:15:30.790
you make enough money,
there's two things.

318
00:15:30.790 --> 00:15:33.760
Number one, maybe you're
more astute investor,

319
00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:34.705
for us maybe not.

320
00:15:34.705 --> 00:15:38.605
But also, you've
got money to lose

321
00:15:38.605 --> 00:15:42.850
and we're not as concerned

322
00:15:42.850 --> 00:15:46.750
there as we are for the
investors of more limited means,

323
00:15:46.750 --> 00:15:50.590
they're the ones that we
want to be careful about not

324
00:15:50.590 --> 00:15:52.990
getting ripped off or at least

325
00:15:52.990 --> 00:15:56.545
not investing to an extent,

326
00:15:56.545 --> 00:15:59.800
not losing a very damaging amount

327
00:15:59.800 --> 00:16:01.720
of money in this market.

328
00:16:01.720 --> 00:16:06.670
So the restrictions from
the entrepreneur side,

329
00:16:06.670 --> 00:16:08.530
I can raise over

330
00:16:08.530 --> 00:16:10.240
any 12-month period up to

331
00:16:10.240 --> 00:16:12.760
$1 million. That's
