406
00:20:00.070 --> 00:20:02.170
If you are doing an IPO,

407
00:20:02.170 --> 00:20:06.640
but there's somewhat lighter
disclosure requirements,

408
00:20:06.640 --> 00:20:08.020
some other lighter
requirements and you're

409
00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:10.045
doing at a smaller size.

410
00:20:10.045 --> 00:20:14.680
So it's a way to allow
a company to do an IPO maybe in

411
00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:17.680
a slightly earlier moment

412
00:20:17.680 --> 00:20:21.530
than they otherwise would
and at a smaller size.

413
00:20:21.530 --> 00:20:26.260
So this really hasn't
taken off so much

414
00:20:26.260 --> 00:20:30.940
the way that the regulators
hoped it would as well.

415
00:20:30.940 --> 00:20:32.170
There's only been
a few of these and

416
00:20:32.170 --> 00:20:34.915
the performance hasn't
