434
00:21:21.670 --> 00:21:25.600
the IPO and then at
the end of that process,

435
00:21:25.600 --> 00:21:27.820
the issuer has sold

436
00:21:27.820 --> 00:21:29.725
whatever shares people
showed up to buy.

437
00:21:29.725 --> 00:21:32.050
So that's a best efforts IPO.

438
00:21:32.050 --> 00:21:34.480
You tend not to see those
for the major companies,

439
00:21:34.480 --> 00:21:38.110
you see this for the
relatively smaller,

440
00:21:38.110 --> 00:21:40.750
sketchy, maybe you
call them companies,

441
00:21:40.750 --> 00:21:42.595
would do a best efforts IPO.

442
00:21:42.595 --> 00:21:46.870
So in this Title IV Reg+ base,

443
00:21:46.870 --> 00:21:48.250
that's also what
you're going to see.

444
00:21:48.250 --> 00:21:49.930
So the retail investor does have

